Level 63 spell,magic based, inherent 0 second stun component.  For some reason, this spell has an interrupt level cap of level 57 mobs, the same as our level 60 and under spells. This doesn't make any sense, seeing as our level 63 stun, Telekin, doesn't have this restriction and can stun mobs well above level 60. The spell needs to be brought up to the level range of Telekin.<br>
<br>
Shock of Magic: <br>
Level 65, ubernukage....maybe....maybe not.  It has a built in random damage generator...anywhere from the low 1k up to the 3k mark. <br>
  It also costs a whopping 600 mana to cast.  I only used it before I had SoS. Very disappointing to blow 600 mana and do 1500 damage. Go me!  The base damage of this spell neesd to be raised to AT LEAST be on par with Agnarr's Thunder in terms of mana/dmg ratio. In it's current incarnation, it's pretty much useless. Fix it, please. <br>
<br>
Greater Decession <br>
This spell is a joke for a glyphed runed word turn in.   With Teleport ( AE TL ) there is no reason to ever mem this spell. Well, maybe <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>once every year</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> someone needs to get to the zone in without me.<br>
<br>
Next, where is our huge ice nuke?  All three resist types need representation in draught to holy-mother-of-god nuke form.  Our *big* nuke is still Ice Spear of Solist. And even with Iceflame, this spell is hokey.  Recast of 15 seconds on a spell in POP? Thanks, but no thanks, I'll stick with E'Ci and Tears of Marr trying to take down mobs in Fire and Sol Ro tower. <br>
<br>
<br>
Lastly, not for nothing, but hopefully this latest patch you did something at least creative to the Strike of Solusek spell effects.  It's the same effect as casting Pillar of Fire, without the joy of 4 beautiful lines of blinding yellow text proclaiming a gain in xp.  This spell is the most consistently powerful DD out there and it's outshadowed by that stupid ranger ice spell with the cool ass rotating ice shards that explode in a beam of light. Damnit, I play with effects on, gimme something to wow folks with.  Maybe something like an arm of plasma reaching down from the sky and washing over your target, splattering into a translucsent glowing image of Solusek Ro as it dissapates. Come on folks, work with us, it is the Strike of Solusek, not the I'm-gonna-whimper-while-I burn-you.<br>
<br>
Other than those issues. we're pretty awesome as a class. Just finish the work you started and everything will be otay. <br>
<br>
